<b>Level 105</b> is the 106<sup>th</sup> level of the backrooms.
__NOTOC__
{{Template:Blurimage|file=MistySky.jpg|caption=The factory and fog seen on the level, taken by agent <span class="spoilerblur">Odessyus Lang</span>. This is the only known image of Level 105.}}
==Description==
<b>Level 105</b> is a massive factory enshrouded in a thick layer of fog surrounded by a grassy field. The level is in a state of perpetual night, with the moon in the sky at all times. Furthermore, a slight drizzle constantly occurs throughout the entire level, and is moderately windy, with temperatures reaching as low as 15 degrees Celsius at times. The field does not seem to possess any particularly strange properties, except for that the blades of grass all seem to be pitch black in colour. Inside of the factory are numerous machines such as conveyor belts, crushers, furnaces and molds, though so far none of them are operational. A factory canteen and an employee break room are also present, which will be explained in detail below.
<br>

This level is roughly 5 kilometres by 7 kilometres, with the edges of this level simply dropping off into what seems to be a void. Additionally, there are several glass chambers, in which contain the same fog, compacted so tightly that it is impossible to view the interior of the chambers. The fog within writhes and turns, sometimes slamming into the glass walls. These chambers have a long tube running from them to nearby smokestacks, and some chambers have cracks running down the side, with one even having a large hole in it, the result of the fog ramming into the glass. Although there are no entities on this level, numerous [[M.E.G.]] agents have gone missing while exploring the level. So far, only one of the four M.E.G. agents dispatched to the level have returned, with the rest presumably being consumed.
<br>

Strangely, no records on the missing M.E.G. agents can be found, as though all mentions of them have been erased, save for an audio file which has not disappeared, and will be provided below. These M.E.G. agents have no information sheets, no recorded expeditions, and none of the existing agents have any recollection of them, though some family members of theirs do remember their existence, which is the only reason the M.E.G. have included this section. This may mean that those who had friends that ventured to this level may have no memory of them. Additionally, the agent that returned safely claims that for half of their expedition, the fog was absent from the level, meaning it may only be present at certain intervals. Due this, traversing this level for prolonged periods is difficult and not recommended, as the intervals which the fog comes and goes is unknown.

==Special Areas==

===Factory Canteen===
The factory canteen is a 100 metre by 50 metre room with benches and tables spread evenly apart throughout the entire room, and a serving counter at the back of the room. Additionally, a kitchen behind the serving counter can be found, containing items such as stoves, ovens, pot and pans, though none of the stoves or ovens are operational. There is a small cooler in one corner of the canteen which contains a stash of [[Object 1|Almond Water]] and restocks at unknown intervals. 

Additionally, this canteen can only be accessed during "break time" which is indicated by the ringing of a bell. When break time is over, wanderers are compelled to leave and the door shuts, locking itself and preventing wanderers from entering. Should wanderers try to break into the canteen when it is not break time, the fog will increase in volume, obscuring vision even more until the wanderer stops.

===Employee Break Room===
The employee break room is a small, 10 metre by 10 metre space furnished with a red carpet, coffee table and a blue couch. There is a mini fridge which contains a few bottles of water that do not restock, so use sparingly. Interestingly enough, the fog seems to not be able to enter the break room, as if there is some invisible force keeping it out. So far, this is the only safe section of the level. It is located in the section of the building near the parking lot and has signs nearby pointing towards it to inform people of its location.

Similar to the canteen, the break room is only accessible during break time. After the break, wanderers will be compelled to leave. If wanderers decide to break into the room, the fog will increase in volume, similar to what occurs when wanderers attempt to break in to the canteen.

===The Cages===
Outside of the factory, cages roughly 3 meters in height are present, and seem to comfortably fit five people in them. The cages have metal bars, however all of the cages seem to have been destroyed, with metal bars deformed and even broken in half in many areas. It is thought that this level was used for some sort of testing, with the experiment having gone awry which led to the subjects escaping. Plaques on each cage can also be seen, all of which state that the cage was containing an entity called the Pzouchix, though it is unknown what this entity could possibly be due to the lack of information.


==Audio Log==
<div class="darkblock">
<span class="spoilerblur">Cecilia Pines</span>: Command, I have reached the level. So far, I can't really see anything above roughly twelve meters above me due to the fog, but it seems like there's some sort of building in front of me. I'm heading in now.
<br>

HQ: Copy that, be careful. The last agent we dispatched didn't return, so there is a suspected entity presence, hence why we set up a walkie-talkie line.
<br>

<span class="spoilerblur">Cecilia Pines</span>: Command, I've entered the building. It seems to be a factory of some sort, there are machines all over the place and the fog is in here as well. God, there's a lot of fog. It's so damn cold, too.
<br>

HQ: Focus, agent. Can you see anything else, besides the machines?
<br>

<span class="spoilerblur">Cecilia Pines</span>: No, I don't see anything else. I'll investigate more and get back to you.
<br>

(Roughly an hour passes)
<br>

<span class="spoilerblur">Cecilia Pines</span>: Command? This is <span class="spoilerblur">Cecilia</span>. I've deduced the level is roughly five klicks by seven klicks long, and the level just... <i>ends</i>. It just drops into the void. I'm in another part of the factory. I think this level is just one, huge factory on a grassy field. There's a parking lot outside.
<br>

HQ: Roger that, agent. Can you find anything else?
<br>

<span class="spoilerblur">Cecilia Pines</span>: The fog is getting denser the longer I stay here. I've found the factory canteen and the employee break room, but nothing of note so far... Wait, I see something on the ground.
<br>

HQ: Can you get closer to it, agent?
<br>

<span class="spoilerblur">Cecilia Pines</span>: Yeah, it's... a piece of paper. Let me read it out for you. "If you're reading this, get out now. The fog isn't what it seems. It's not wind. It's already eaten Jake and... God, I forgot his name. Why can't I remember his name? Whatever, just get out fast, from whatever exit has been found."
<br>

(Silence)
<br>

HQ: ...Agent?
<br>

<span class="spoilerblur">Cecilia Pines</span>: Command... that's not wind. God, I... I can hear <span class="spoilerblur">Odessyus</span>. He's screaming my name, begging me to run.
<br>

HQ: Get out of there, agent! Hello? Agent? 

<span class="spoilerblur">Cecilia Pines</span>: ...The fog is coming.
<br>
(Only wind and rain can be heard for over three hours before communication is cut from <span class="spoilerblur">Cecilia Pines'</span> end.)</div>

==Entities==
So far, no entities have been spotted, but it is theorised that the fog on this level may be an entity itself, though there are no possible answers as to why all memory of a person is erased when they are consumed by the fog. Furthermore, some surviving wanderers have claimed to have seen human faces in the fog, though this is unconfirmed.

==Colonies, bases and outposts==
Due to the nature of this level, no bases can be established here.

==Entrances and Exits==
===Entrances===
*Entering any building in [[Level 11]] has a chance to bring wanderers here.
*Wanderers that pass out and survive overexposure from the sulfur dioxide gas present in the air of [[Level 127]] will bring wanderers here. 
*No-clipping into the ground on any foggy level will bring wanderers here.

===Exits===
*The primary egress is to wait for the fog to dissipate, then no-clipping into one of the broken cages outside to be sent to [[Level 200]].
*Alternatively, one may noclip through a log to enter [[Level 416]].
